However, Sharon said Syria has to show its will and terminate terrorism before the two countries can resume peace talks.
(International) South Korea President Said Relation of Two Koreas Has Improved
Xinhua News Agency, Seoul, January 14 (Reporter: Zhang Li) - South Korea President Roh Moo-hyun said on the 14th that the relationship between the two Koreas has "slow but realistic" progress in the past year despite impacts of the nuclear problem.  South Korea will continue to develop South-North relation, including practical issues, this year on top of its solid foundation in national security.
