The book On Social Investigations and Studies by Mao Zedong, Zhou Enlai, Liu Shaoqi, Zhu De, Deng Xiaoping and Chen Yun consists of three parts: part one is a selection of quotations on social investigations and studies by Mao Zedong and other veteran revolutionaries; part two consists of writings on social investigations and studies by Mao Zedong and other veteran revolutionaries; and part three consists of investigative reports written by the three investigation teams designated by Mao Zedong in the early 1960s as well as by Liu Shaoqi, Zhou Enlai, Zhu De, Chen Yun, Deng Xiaoping and others.
