The largest animation festival in South America is held in the capital of Peru, Lima.
This event is held by local animation fans in Peru and lasts for four days. It is expected to attract 100,000 visitors.
According to the report on November 5 of Japan’s NHK, the activity contents of this animation festival are rich and colorful, including American anime role shows, talk shows of Spanish dubber of the popular Japanese anime "Dragon Ball", a karaoke contest of Japanese animation theme song, a animation role play competition, etc. All activities are splendid.
